---
// Static editorial content for FTMO
// Supports multiple sections via the `section` prop
interface Props {
  section: string;
  fallbackBody?: string;
}
const { section, fallbackBody } = Astro.props;
---

{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* CHALLENGES SECTION                                                  */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "challenges" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <!-- Overview -->
  <p class="mb-4">
    FTMO now offers two evaluation products &mdash; <strong>FTMO Challenge: 2-Step</strong> and <strong>FTMO Challenge: 1-Step</strong>. All FTMO Challenge accounts are simulated accounts with fictitious funds, and trading is not in real financial instruments. FTMO is an educational and technology-driven company offering simulated trading environments, not a broker.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Current entry pricing starts at <strong>&euro;89</strong> for the $10,000 2-Step challenge. The FTMO Challenge fee is a one-time refundable fee &mdash; you receive a 100% refund of your initial fee with your first reward withdrawal.
  </p>

  <!-- Fee Table -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">2-Step Challenge Fees</h3>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <thead class="bg-slate-800 text-xs font-semibold text-white uppercase tracking-wide">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Account Size</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Challenge Fee</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$10,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">&euro;89</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$25,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">&euro;250</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$50,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">&euro;345</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$100,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">&euro;439</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$200,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">&euro;1,080</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Evaluation Products -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Evaluation Products</h3>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- 2-STEP                                                          -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="mb-8">
    <h4 class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-500 text-white text-xs font-black flex items-center justify-center">1</span>
      FTMO Challenge: 2-Step
    </h4>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The 2-Step evaluation consists of the <strong>FTMO Challenge</strong> (Phase 1) and <strong>Verification</strong> (Phase 2). The trading period is <strong>unlimited</strong>, with a minimum of <strong>4 trading days</strong> per phase. Max Daily Loss is <strong>5% of initial balance</strong> and resets daily from midnight CE(S)T account balance context. Max Loss is <strong>10% of initial balance</strong>.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2 mb-3">
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Phase 1 Target</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">10%</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Phase 2 Target</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">5%</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Max Daily Loss</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">5%</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Max Loss</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">10%</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mb-4">
      On the FTMO Account, 2-Step rewards start at <strong>80%</strong> and can increase to <strong>90%</strong> through the Scaling Plan.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- 1-STEP                                                          -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="mb-8">
    <h4 class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-500 text-white text-xs font-black flex items-center justify-center">2</span>
      FTMO Challenge: 1-Step
    </h4>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The 1-Step evaluation is a single-phase challenge. The Maximum Daily Loss is <strong>3%</strong> and the Maximum Loss is <strong>10%</strong>, calculated as a trailing-style drawdown based on the highest end-of-day balance or initial balance, whichever is higher. Minimum <strong>4 trading days</strong> required.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The 1-Step includes a <strong>Best Day Rule</strong>: the most profitable day cannot exceed <strong>50% of Positive Days' Profit</strong> when passing the challenge or qualifying for a reward.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2 mb-3">
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Profit Target</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">10%</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Max Daily Loss</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">3%</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Max Loss (Trailing)</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">10%</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
        <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Best Day Rule</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-bold text-amber-600">50% cap</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mb-4">
      On the FTMO Account for 1-Step, the reward is <strong>90%</strong> of simulated profits.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- ACCOUNT TYPES                                                    -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Account Types: Standard vs Swing</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Both 1-Step and 2-Step challenges offer <strong>Standard</strong> and <strong>Swing</strong> account types. These determine the trading conditions on the FTMO Account, not during the evaluation phase.
  </p>

  <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm whitespace-nowrap">
      <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Condition</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Standard</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Swing</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Overnight Holding (FTMO Account)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">&#10007;</span></td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center"><span class="text-teal-600 font-bold">&#10003;</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Weekend Holding (FTMO Account)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">&#10007;</span></td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center"><span class="text-teal-600 font-bold">&#10003;</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">News Trading (FTMO Account)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center"><span class="text-red-400 font-bold">&#10007;</span> <span class="text-xs text-slate-500">2-min rule</span></td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center"><span class="text-teal-600 font-bold">&#10003;</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">During Evaluation</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center" colspan="2"><span class="text-xs text-slate-600">These restrictions do not apply during evaluation</span></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-amber-400 bg-amber-50/60 px-5 py-4 mb-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Important:</strong> Overnight, weekend, and news restrictions apply only to the <strong>Standard account type</strong> and only once on the <strong>FTMO Account</strong>, not during the evaluation phase. The 1-Step evaluation allows news trading freely during macroeconomic releases. Swing accounts have no overnight, weekend, or news restrictions at any stage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── Scaling Plan ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Scaling Plan</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    FTMO's Scaling Plan increases account balance by <strong>25% per scale-up</strong>. To qualify, traders must complete a minimum <strong>4-month cycle</strong>, achieve at least <strong>10% total net simulated profit</strong> in the 4-month trading window, have at least <strong>2 rewards processed</strong>, and maintain a <strong>positive balance</strong> at time of scale-up.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Traders can reach a maximum FTMO Account allocation of <strong>$400,000</strong> before scaling. The Scaling Plan can grow accounts up to <strong>$2,000,000</strong>. 2-Step rewards start at 80% and the Scaling Plan upgrades to <strong>90%</strong>.
  </p>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2 mb-8">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Scale-Up Amount</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-teal-600">25%</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Min Cycle</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">4 months</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Max Allocation</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-teal-600">$2,000,000</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Max Reward Split</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-teal-600">90%</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── Other Rules ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Other Rules</h3>
  <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">News Trading Restriction (Standard FTMO Account only)</p>
      <p>Cannot open or close trades on targeted instruments within <strong>2 minutes</strong> before or after high-impact news releases. This applies only to the Standard account type on the FTMO Account, not during evaluation. Swing accounts are exempt.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Trade Access</p>
      <p>Only the client may access and perform simulated trades. Third parties cannot trade for you or manage your account.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Phase Evaluation</p>
      <p>FTMO will not evaluate a phase until all simulated trades and pending orders are closed.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Multiple Accounts</p>
      <p>The total Initial Simulated Capital across accounts held by you or affiliated parties cannot exceed <strong>$400,000</strong> during the evaluation process.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Automation</p>
      <p>FTMO platforms support automation tools such as EAs on supported platforms, but trading remains subject to FTMO's forbidden trading practices and risk management rules.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Simulated environment callout -->
  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-amber-400 bg-amber-50/60 px-5 py-4 mb-6">
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Simulated environment:</strong> All FTMO Challenge accounts are simulated accounts with fictitious funds. Trading is not in real financial instruments. FTMO is an educational and technology-driven company, not a broker.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Verdict -->
  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-teal-500 bg-teal-50/60 px-5 py-4">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-800 mb-1">Verdict on FTMO Challenges</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      FTMO offers two evaluation products &mdash; 1-Step and 2-Step &mdash; with fees starting from &euro;89 for the $10,000 2-Step challenge. The 2-Step provides an unlimited trading period with standard drawdown rules, while the 1-Step uses a tighter 3% daily loss limit, trailing max loss, and the Best Day Rule. Account flexibility comes from Standard vs Swing conditions, and the Scaling Plan can grow accounts up to $2,000,000.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>
)}

{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* SPREADS / COMMISSION FEES & PRICING SECTION                         */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "spreads" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <p class="mb-6">
    FTMO offers RAW spreads across its trading platforms. All FTMO Challenge accounts are simulated accounts with fictitious funds, and the trading environment is designed to provide competitive execution conditions.
  </p>

  <!-- Commission Info -->
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Commission Structure</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    The official FTMO Symbols page shows a commission of <strong>$5.000</strong> on listed forex pairs. Commission rates may vary by instrument and should be verified against the current official symbol specifications on the FTMO Symbols page before trading.
  </p>

  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-amber-400 bg-amber-50/60 px-5 py-4 mb-6">
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Note:</strong> Specific spread and commission figures should be verified against the current official FTMO Symbols page, as these may change over time.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Verdict -->
  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-teal-500 bg-teal-50/60 px-5 py-4">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-800 mb-1">Verdict on Spreads &amp; Commissions</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      FTMO provides RAW spreads with commission-based pricing. Traders should check the official FTMO Symbols page for the latest spread and commission details on specific instruments. FTMO scored 8/10 for spreads.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>
)}

{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* MARKETS / FINANCIAL MARKETS & LEVERAGE SECTION                      */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "markets" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <p class="mb-6">
    FTMO provides access to multiple asset classes. The official FTMO Symbols page lists <strong>Forex, Indices, Crypto, and Commodities</strong>, with platform descriptions also referring to multi-asset access including stocks and bonds.
  </p>

  <!-- Market Categories -->
  <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Forex</p>
      <p>Major, minor, and exotic currency pairs available for trading.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Indices</p>
      <p>Global indices including major benchmarks like US30, GER40, and UK100.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Commodities</p>
      <p>Precious metals and energy products including gold, silver, and crude oil.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Cryptocurrencies</p>
      <p>Crypto pairs including BTC/USD and ETH/USD.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Stocks &amp; Bonds</p>
      <p>Additional asset classes available on supported platforms. Check the official FTMO Symbols page for the current list of available instruments.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-amber-400 bg-amber-50/60 px-5 py-4 mb-6">
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Note:</strong> Specific instrument counts and leverage figures should be verified against the current official FTMO challenge setup page, as these may change between products and account types.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Verdict -->
  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-teal-500 bg-teal-50/60 px-5 py-4">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-800 mb-1">Verdict on Markets</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      FTMO provides access to a diverse range of asset classes including forex, indices, commodities, crypto, stocks, and bonds across four trading platforms. FTMO scored 8/10 for markets.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>
)}

{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* PLATFORMS / TRADING PLATFORMS SECTION                                */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "platforms" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <p class="mb-6">
    FTMO offers four trading platforms: <strong>MetaTrader 4 (MT4)</strong>, <strong>MetaTrader 5 (MT5)</strong>, <strong>cTrader</strong>, and <strong>DXtrade</strong>. Each platform offers unique features tailored to different trading needs.
  </p>

  <!-- Platform cards -->
  <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">MetaTrader 4 (MT4)</p>
      <p>The most popular forex trading platform globally. Supports automated trading via Expert Advisors (EAs) with over 15,000 available. Includes 30 built-in indicators, 9 timeframes, and 24 analytical objects (Fibonacci, Gann tools). Available on desktop, web, and mobile.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">MetaTrader 5 (MT5)</p>
      <p>Enhanced version with 38 built-in indicators, 21 timeframes, 44 analytical objects, an economic calendar, and real-time market news. Suitable for trading a wider range of asset classes. Available on desktop, web, and mobile.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">cTrader</p>
      <p>Multi-asset platform known for advanced trading features and intuitive interface. Offers Depth of Market (DOM), algorithmic trading through cBots, comprehensive backtesting, and one-click trading. Available on desktop, web, and mobile.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
      <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">DXtrade</p>
      <p>Multi-asset platform with advanced charting tools, risk management systems, and order management capabilities. Known for flexibility and a modern, user-friendly interface. <strong>Web-only</strong> &mdash; no desktop or mobile application.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Verdict -->
  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-teal-500 bg-teal-50/60 px-5 py-4">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-800 mb-1">Verdict on Trading Platforms</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
      FTMO's platform offering of MT4, MT5, cTrader, and DXtrade ensures that traders have access to a wide range of tools and features, regardless of their trading style or experience level. FTMO scored 9/10 for platforms.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>
)}

{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{/* PAYOUTS / PAYMENTS & PROFIT PAYOUT SECTION                          */}
{/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
{section === "payouts" && (
<div class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">

  <p class="mb-6">
    FTMO provides a variety of payment options and flexible reward structures. FTMO calls its payouts "rewards" &mdash; all rewards are based on simulated profits from fictitious funds.
  </p>

  <!-- Payout overview -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2 mb-8">
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">2-Step Reward</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">80% &rarr; 90%</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">1-Step Reward</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-teal-600">90%</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">First Reward After</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800">14 days</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 px-3 py-2">
      <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Processing Time</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-bold text-teal-600">Avg 8 hours</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Reward Structure -->
